@st-pasha It's how the Jenkins UI works. We specify three "tasks" executed in parallel (x86_64_centos7, x86_64_linux, x86_64_macos). Each of these consists of multiple stages (build, coverage, test py35, test py36) however these stages are not displayed in BlueOcean UI, but if you check then "traditional" UI, you will see something like:
